<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1362,1963]" pageId="20" pageNumber="493">Male genitalia. Pygofer ventral appendage absent. Subgenital plate curved evenly dorsad, distal section weakly pigmented dorsolaterally; dorsal callosity relatively large and oblique. Style with preapical lobe very small, preapical heel absent. Aedeagus in lateral view with preatrium slightly shorter than shaft, evenly curved dorsad; shaft robust, curved dorsad, with weak lateral anterodorsaly at apex; in posterior view with preatrium broader than shaft and nearly quadrate, shaft slightly constricted at base, atrial processes very short and broad.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
